== history -r <file> merges the named file into the list:
    1  existing one
    2  existing two
    3  merged alpha
    4  merged beta
== history -r on a missing file errors:
shit: 1:9: error: Builtin `history`: cannot read history from '/no/such/history/file': No such file or directory.
     1 |  history -r /no/such/history/file; echo "rc=$?"
       |          ^~ here.
shit: note: Pass a readable history file, e.g. `history -r ~/.shit_history`.
rc=1
